Course 1 "Foundations of Robot Motion" - Module 1 "Introduction to Modern Robotics"

NOTE: This guide/note packet uses Python not MATLAB or Mathematica

Useful Links: 
             Website - https://hades.mech.northwestern.edu/index.php/Modern_Robotics
             Textbook - https://hades.mech.northwestern.edu/images/2/2e/MR-largefont-v2.pdf
             GitHub - https://github.com/NxRLab/ModernRobotics

How to Get MR Library:
  1. Install Python at https://www.python.org/downloads/
  2. Create a folder on Desktop
  3. Open folder in powershell
  4. Run commands:
     - "python -m venv env" creates virtual environment
     - "env\Scripts\activate" activates virtual environment
     - "pip install numpy" installs numpy into the virtual environment (required for MR Library)
     - "pip install modern_robotics" installs the MR Library into the virtual environment

Using MR Library:
  1. Install Visual Studio Code
  2. In your folder create a .py file
  3. run "import modern_robotics as mr" to import the library
  4. Code...

Installing CoppeliaSim:
  1. Install CoppeliaSim EDU at https://www.coppeliarobotics.com/
  2. Download scenes at https://hades.mech.northwestern.edu/images/3/31/CoppeliaSim_scenes-Nov2024.zip
  3. Unzip them to your folder

Note to remember: Professor Lynch uses his left hand to show the right hand rule due to the video being reversed
